cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image generation. It also involves the use of deep generative models, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper proposes a new method for few-shot image generation, which involves matching random vectors with a few conditional images, indicating the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also involves the use of discriminators, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on three datasets, indicating the use of multimedia (cs.MM) techniques.
